Date: 0/0/1949
Source: Sheep and Sheepmen of Canterbury
Author: CRAWFORD
Vol / Page: 42
Edition:
Quote: Later [? after washing] the sheep were driven into `the soak', a sort of bath about twenty feet long by ten feet wide let into the ground beside a creek. It was filled and kept full of lukewarm water to which soap and sometimes ammonia were added.
